 **RENT**
A. BASE RENT.
Tenant shall pay to Landlord as base rent ("Base Rent") during the Term the sum of
One Hundred Thousand and 00/100 Dollars ($100,000.00) per annum, payable in equal
monthly installments of Eight Thousand Three Hundred Thirty-Three and 33/100 Dollars
($8,333.33) in advance on the first day of each month during the Term, without any setoff or
deduction whatsoever, except as otherwise provided in this Lease.

B. TAX RENT.
1. Tax Rent Due Date.
Tenant shall pay to Landlord as additional rent ("Tax Rent") an amount equal to the
Property Taxes for each fiscal year of the taxing authority, payable in equal monthly
installments on the first day of each month during the Term, without any setoff or deduction
whatsoever, except as otherwise provided in this Lease. The first installment of Tax Rent shall
be due on the first day of the month following the commencement of the Term and shall be
based on the Property Taxes for the then-current fiscal year of the taxing authority. Each
installment of Tax Rent thereafter shall be based on the Property Taxes for the then-current
fiscal year of the taxing authority.

